popularityCurve.label: dr paolo matthiae director of the italian archeological mission in syria discovered the greatest third-millennium from 2500 b c archive ever unearthed it included more than 15 000 cuneiform tablets and fragments and unveiled a semitic empire that dominated the middle east more than four thousand years ago its hub was ebla where educated scribes filled their ancient libraries with written records of history people places and commerce
